How to Debug your Waku dApp #  Enable Debug Logs #  JS-Waku and its most relevant dependencies (libp2p) uses debug to handle logs.
NodeJS #  To enable debug logs when running js-waku with NodeJS, simply set the DEBUG environment variable.
To only enable js-waku debug logs:
export DEBUG=waku* To enable js-waku and libp2p debug logs:
export DEBUG=waku*,libp2p* To enable all debug logs:
export DEBUG=* Browser #  To see the debug logs in your browser&rsquo;s console, you need to modify the local storage and add debug key.
